The robot supports accurate backward motion using rotary encoder feedback. The travelled distance is calculated from encoder pulses, allowing the robot to reverse a predefined distance before performing the next navigation action.

### Demonstration

![Backward Movement](images/backward_movement_execution.png)</span></code></pre></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="799" data-end="802">
<p data-start="804" data-end="845">One thing I noticed from your screenshot:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="847" data-end="893"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="contents"><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-(--code-block-surface) corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl [--code-block-surface:var(--bg-elevated-secondary)] dark:[--code-block-surface:var(--composer-surface-primary)] lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button type="button" class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-c728a27e.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="relative"><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼd ͼr"><div class="cm-scroller"><pre class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly m-0"><code><span>NameError: name 'clear' is not defined</span></code></pre></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="895" data-end="1250">That appears in the <strong data-start="915" data-end="928">Assistant</strong> pane of Thonny and doesn't match the shell output shown below it. Since the robot output in the shell is running normally, I'd <strong data-start="1056" data-end="1079">crop the screenshot</strong> to remove the right-hand "Assistant" panel before uploading it to GitHub. That way, recruiters will only see the successful execution output and not an unrelated warning.</p>
<p data-start="1252" data-end="1284">A cleaner screenshot would show:</p>
<ul data-start="1285" data-end="1420">
<li data-section-id="9fygch" data-start="1285" data-end="1320">
<p data-start="1287" data-end="1320"><code data-start="1287" data-end="1300">backward.py</code> open in the editor.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="x8b6ox" data-start="1321" data-end="1385">
<p data-start="1323" data-end="1385">The shell displaying distance measurements and encoder output.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="bd8lrx" data-start="1386" data-end="1420">
<p data-start="1388" data-end="1420">No Assistant panel on the right.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1422" data-end="1473" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">That presents the project much more professionally.</p></div></div></div></div><div class="z-0 flex min-h-[46px] justify-start"><div aria-label="Response actions" class="touch:-me-2 touch:-ms-3.5 -ms-2.5 -me-1 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-y-4 p-1 select-none touch:w-[calc(100%+--spacing(3.5))] -mt-1 w-[calc(100%+--spacing(2.5))] duration-[1.5s] focus-within:transition-none hover:transition-none touch:pointer-events-auto pointer-events-none [mask-image:linear-gradient(to_right,black_33%,transparent_66%)] [mask-size:300%_100%] [mask-position:100%_0%] motion-safe:transition-[mask-position] group-hover/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-hover/turn-messages:[mask-position:0_0] group-focus-within/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-focus-within/turn-messages:[mask-position:0_0] has-data-[state=open]:pointer-events-auto has-data-[state=open]:[mask-position:0_0]" role="group" tabindex="-1" style="mask-position: 0% 0%;"><button type="button" class="text-token-text-secondary hover:bg-token-surface-hover rounded-lg" aria-label="Copy response" data-testid="copy-turn-action-button" data-state="closed"><span class="flex items-center justify-center touch:w-10 h-8 w-8"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-c728a27e.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></span></button><button type="button" class="text-token-text-secondary hover:bg-token-surface-hover rounded-lg" aria-label="Humanize with Quillbot" data-testid="quillbot-humanize-button" data-state="closed" data-quillbot-humanize-button="true" style="display: inline-flex;" title="Humanize with Quillbot"><span class="flex items-center justify-center touch:w-10 h-8 w-8"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
